# =============================================================================
# Newsletter Builder Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
# 
# IMPORTANT: All configuration is now handled CLIENT-SIDE for complete security
# and public deployment. Users configure everything in the app interface.
# No server-side secrets required!
#

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Kit.com Configuration (OPTIONAL - for server defaults)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Template ID used for formatting exports (can be overridden by users)
KIT_EMAIL_TEMPLATE_ID=2

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# App Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# =============================================================================
# Client-Side Configuration (Set by Users in App):
# =============================================================================
# 
# Users configure all of these directly in the app interface:
# 
# 1. GitHub Repository Configuration:
#    - GitHub Username (owner)
#    - Repository Name  
#    - Branch (defaults to 'main')
#    - Personal Access Token with repo permissions
# 
# 2. OpenAI Configuration:
#    - API Key with GPT-4 access (REQUIRED for newsletter generation)
# 
# 3. Kit.com Configuration (OPTIONAL):
#    - API Key for direct publishing
#
# =============================================================================
# Setup Instructions for Public Deployment:
# =============================================================================
# 
# 1. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL to your deployment URL
# 2. Optionally set KIT_EMAIL_TEMPLATE_ID (defaults to 2)
# 3. Deploy anywhere - no other configuration needed!
#
# Users will configure their own:
# - GitHub repository (username/repo-name/branch)
# - GitHub Personal Access Token
# - OpenAI API Key
# - Kit.com API Key (optional)
#
# This makes the deployment completely secure and allows unlimited public access. 